        <div>
          <h3>How to Choose a Cat</h3>
          <p>There are many considerations when picking the right cat for you. 
            Knowing the answers to the questions below should help you decide.</p>
          <h4>Kitten or Adult?</h4>
          <p>Kittens have tons of energy and demand tons of attention. They come house-trained, so no need to worry about that.
            However, you will have to keep your kitten busy. Kittens may need extra toys to keep them busy.</p>
          <h4>Short or Long Hair?</h4>
          <p>Short haired cats need little to no grooming as they keep themselves clearn. 
            Long haired cats will need daily or weekly brushing depending on the coat.
          They may also leave more hairballs around the house as presents for you!</p>
          <h4>Personality</h4>
          <p>Bengals are quirky and wild. They also tend to be more independent.
          Savannah cats need to go outside on a leash as they're as big as a labrador!
          Siamese can be big talkers. Make sure you know your breed's characteristics before you choose.</p>
          <h4>Allergies</h4>
          <p>Spend some time with a cat to make sure you and your family are not allergic before you buy.</p>
